    // Gjs wrapper for g_file_monitor()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Obtains a file or directory monitor for the given file,
depending on the type of the file.</p>  <p>If <code>cancellable</code> is not <code>null</code>, then the operation can be cancelled by
triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation
was cancelled, the error <link xref="Gio.IOErrorEnum"/>.cancelled will be returned.</p>
  <p>Since 2.18</p>
